NAME
     archiveutil – command-line interface for the Archive Utility application.

SYNOPSIS
     archiveutil command [options]

DESCRIPTION
     archiveutil is a command-line utility for working with archive files on
     macOS. It provides various operations for extracting and manipulating
     archive formats.

COMMANDS
     extractXcodeAEA path
              Extract an Xcode AEA (Apple Encrypted Archive) file at the
              specified path.

EXAMPLES
     Extract an Xcode AEA archive:

           $ archiveutil extractXcodeAEA /path/to/Xcode.aea

SEE ALSO
     ditto(1), tar(1), zip(1), unzip(1)

HISTORY
     The archiveutil utility first appeared in macOS 15.0.

